\id 2TH - Plain English Version 
\h 2 Thessalonians 
\toc2 2 Thessalonians 
\toc1 Paul’s 2nd Letter to the Thessalonians 
\mt1 The 2nd letter that Paul wrote to the Christians at Thessalonica  
\mt2 (The book in the Holy Bible called \bk 2 Thessalonians\bk*)  
\imt1 About this letter  
\ip Paul wrote this letter about 2,000 years ago, about 20 years after Jesus went back to heaven, and it is now in the Holy Bible.  
\ip After Jesus went back to heaven, God sent Paul to lots of countries and lots of towns to tell people about Jesus. One of those towns was Thessalonica (see Acts 17:1-9). It was a big town in the country called Greece, where the Greek people come from, and it is still there today. Sometimes people now call that town Salonica.  
\ip Paul wrote his 1st letter to the Christians at Thessalonica soon after he left there. Then about 6 months later, Paul heard that there were people making trouble for those new Christians at Thessalonica and telling them that Jesus already came back from heaven. So Paul wrote this 2nd letter to them, to tell them the true story about what will happen on the earth before Jesus comes back.  
\ip Paul said a lot of important things in this letter, so today we have to take notice of what he wrote to the Christians at Thessalonica.  
\cl Chapter  
\c 1  
\p
